Here's what I did when updating to Argo CD v2.3.0

Hello. This is the riddle of the SRE group of mixi's development headquarters .

Argo CD v2.3.0 has been released! 🙌🙌

  • Argo CD v2.3 release candidate.
  • argo-cd/2.2–2.3.md at v2.3.0 · argoproj/argo-cd

Since the version was upgraded immediately, I will introduce the procedure that was carried out.

<Table of Contents>

  1. Prerequisite information
  2. Argo CD v2.3.0 update
  3. Work contents
    3.1 Impact investigation of Kustomize / Helm version upgrade
    3.2 Schema generation
    3.3 Removal of old Argo CD Notifications
    3.4 Update to Argo CD v2.3.0
    3.5 Export HELM_EXPERIMENTAL_OCI = 1 removal
    3.6 RespectIgnoreDifferences setting
  4. summary

Prerequisite information

Click here for environmental information when we upgraded.

  • v2.2.3Updated to → v2.3.0.
  • v1.1.0I'm using Argo CD Notifications ( ).
  • kubeconformThe schema is checked by.
  • You are using an OCI-compliant Artifact Registry to store Helm packages.

Argo CD v2.3.0 update

Here is a list of updates that needed to be addressed in our case.

  • Argo CD Notifications / ApplicationSet have been aggregated into one repository.
  • KustomizeVersion upgrade in Argo CD ( v4.2.0→ v4.4.1)
  • HelmVersion upgrade in Argo CD ( v3.7.1→ v3.8.0)
  • Introducing the new Sync And Diff Strategies ( RespectIgnoreDifferences/managedFieldsManagers).

Work content

I proceeded with the work in the following order.

  1. KustomizeImpact investigation of / Helmupgrade to existing manifest
  2. Generate schema for schema check from updated CRD
  3. Removed old Argo CD Notifications
  4. Updated to Argo CD v2.3.0
  5. export HELM_EXPERIMENTAL_OCI=1Delete
  6. RespectIgnoreDifferencessettings of

[Procedure 1] Impact investigation of Kustomize / Helm version upgrade

Kustomize / HelmAfter seeing the GitHub Release of, to understand the changes

  • Can a manifest be generated?
  • Is the generated manifest different from the current state?

Confirmed (in our case there were no diffs or problems).

However, depending on the environment, you may want to use a specific version of KustomizeYa . HelmIn that case, specify the version in the Argo CD settings.

Reference: kustomize has been upgraded to v4.4.0

[Procedure 2] Schema generation

We are kubeconformdoing a schema check for the manifest at.

So I had to generate a new CRD schema, but it was automated and it was easy (useful!).

Here is an article that introduces schema automation.

  • Let's enjoy automatically generating the schema used in kubeconform with GitHub Action!

[Procedure 3] Delete old Argo CD Notifications

I just deleted the app that is currently running on k8s. I'm using an Argo CD, so ApplicationI removed the corresponding one and let GitOps do the rest.

[Procedure 4] Update to Argo CD v2.3.0

I got the manifest of Argo CD v2.3.0 by the following method and stored it in Git.

Once you've moved the old Argo CD Notifications settings here , commit and let GitOps do the rest. This is all you need to do to upgrade (easy!).

* In our case, the ConfigMap ( argocd-notifications-cm) used in the old Argo CD Notifications could be used as it is.

[Procedure 5] Delete export HELM_EXPERIMENTAL_OCI = 1

Due to the fact that we manage manifests in two different repositories, we store Helm packages in the Artifact Registry on Google Cloud.

* For details , see How to deploy with ArgoCD when Helm values ​​and Chart are in different repositories .

If you store it in the Artifact Registry, you must generate the Helm package as an OCI-compliant image.

Creating an OCI-compliant image is an experimental feature and Helm 3.7.1should export HELM_EXPERIMENTAL_OCI=1be tapped.

However, the Argo CD v2.3.0 included Helm 3.8.0can now create OCI-compliant images by default, and the HELM_EXPERIMENTAL_OCI=1settings could be removed.

[Procedure 6] Set RespectIgnoreDifferences

RespectIgnoreDifferencesBefore explaining, I will introduce "How Argo CD performs synchronization ignoring differences" to understand the operation .

With this Applicationsetting

DeploymentSuppose you are managing Nginx .

The Argo CD has a setting that intentionally ignores the diff . ignoreDifferences

Setting this ignores in, so even if HPA spec.ignoreDifferences[].jsonPointerschanges Deploymentto 2, Argo CD will not sync with Git.replicasreplicas

However Deployment, metadata/labelsif you get a commit that changes something, the Argo CD will replicasupdate with the settings that you should have ignored, so replicaswill return to 1.

This causes the HPA replicasto return to 2 again.

* HPA is taken as an example, but any app or tool that controls the parameters of Argo CD management is OK.

replicasTo prevent the Argo CD from updating HPA-managed , the Argo CD documentation introduces a workaround that says " Do replicasnot include in manifests ".

Like this ↓

However , this method does not work with external Helm charts or kustomization.yamlreplicas that have embedded .

It's been a long time, but it RespectIgnoreDifferences's a story from here. This update adds two features that work around this issue .

  1. The ignore target of Argo CD ignoreDifferencesis also used at sync ( sync option(RespectIgnoreDifferences=true)).
  2. Argo CD ignores (specifies with) manifest differences from a particular ignoreDifferencescontroller managedFieldsManagers.

※refer to※

  • New sync and diff strategies in ArgoCD
  • https://github.com/argoproj/argo-cd/issues/2913#issuecomment-978001260

Either way, the HPA example above can be avoided, but we have RespectIgnoreDifferencesset it to be easy to use.

syncPolicy.syncOptions[].RespectIgnoreDifferences=trueIt's easy because you only need to set.

summary

Thank you for your hard work.

There are various changes even if the minor version is upgraded by one, but there are security risks if it remains old, so let's do our best to update it!

Thanks again for making a useful product Argo CD Community🙏
